com.camerontec.util.datamodel

Interface Encoder<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - target representation
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FIXFieldValueEncoder

    public interface Encoder<T>
    Interface to be implemented by objects capable of encoding all data types to a target representation.

      • encodeDouble

        int encodeDouble(double value,
                 T target,
                 int index)
        Encode a double value.

        Warning: Java doubles are not precise representations and therefore may not be encoded as expected. Specifically, doubles should never be used for precise values like currency. Use java.math.BigDecimal instead.

        Parameters:
        value - The value.
        target - The target.
        index - The index into the target at which to encode.
        Returns:
        The number of bytes encoded.
